sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1399013
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Lactose/IPTG inducible promoter with RFP reporter tagged with DAS-ssrA degradation tag followed by terminator. The tagged RFP is degraded within cell, thus provides better temporal resolution of red fluorescence and promoter activity. Presence of SspB is crucial for effective protein degradation.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Anna Stikane
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Part was assembled using BrickClip assembly (BBF RFC104) using other biobrick parts as templates. BrickClip assembly is a special case of more general Paperclip assembly method.[1]
